The Commodity Futures TradingCommission, CFTC, said that on April 15 it will consider theChicago Board of Trade's proposal to establish night trading.    The Chicago exchange hopes to begin night trading at theend of the month. The proposed trading session -- which wouldbe the first in the United States -- would extend from 1700 to2100 local time (2300 to 0300 GMT).    CFTC also said that on April 22 it will consider thePhiladelphia Board of Trade's application to trade futures onthe Australian dollar and the New York Cotton Exchange'sapplication to trade the five-year U.S. Treasury Index. Reuter&#3;